1. Data Collection

The dataset is loaded using Pandas and inspected to understand its structure.


2. Data Exploration (EDA)

Exploratory Data Analysis is performed to understand data distribution and relationships between features.

Steps include:

Checking dataset shape

Checking missing values

Visualizing fraud vs normal transactions

Creating correlation heatmap


3. Data Preprocessing

The dataset is prepared for machine learning by:

Separating features and target variable

Converting data into NumPy arrays

4. Handling Imbalanced Data

Since fraud transactions are very rare, techniques like sampling or anomaly detection may be applied.


5. Model Training

Machine learning algorithms are trained using the training dataset.

Common models used:

Logistic Regression

Random Forest

Decision Tree


6. Model Evaluation

The trained model is evaluated using testing data.

Evaluation metrics include:

Accuracy

Precision

Recall

F1 Score

Confusion Matrix

These metrics help determine how well the model detects fraudulent transactions.

